<subSubSection id="E820C87FB1C324C07DA984697E105AFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="8EB2AF2C53618D34BC4126FDB1864E21" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CAC62C6F015E8FDF096D5262D93E1978" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Found upon its pink host sponge, 
<taxonomicName id="CE6957BEB9612C3D00F337AF840CECD0" class="Insecta" family="Promecheilidae" genus="Darwinella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darwinella" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF2E8D416C271BC8DDE54A8E136D1E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Darwinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., at deeper reef and pinnacle sites, and in muck habitats. Depth 12-30 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC312F419745DBB2350F649C577692C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5D1AEEA7E2AF6E6A4A9DD95FA3E9DA2D" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F3233C0CB89BB589E86C9D1D412AED30" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Red Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="A45E4DFC98B85EB6BC4C87080BBF8170" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" author="Yonow, N" editor="Rasul, NMA" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="531 - 550" refId="B289" refString="Yonow, N, 2015. Sea Slugs: unexpected biodiversity and distribution. In: Rasul, NMA, Stewart, ICF, Eds., The Red Sea. Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg: 531 - 550, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" title="Sea Slugs: unexpected biodiversity and distribution." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-662-45201-1_30" volumeTitle="The Red Sea." year="2015">Yonow 2015</bibRefCitation>
), South Africa, Tanzania, Australia, and Hong Kong (
<bibRefCitation id="9873A555EE0A9F19E06FF674BBFE4549" author="Gosliner, TM" journalOrPublisher="Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" refId="B94" refString="Gosliner, TM, Behrens, D, Valdes, A, 2008. Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna. Sea Challengers Natural History Books, Gig Harbor" title="Indo-Pacific nudibranchs and sea slugs: a field guide to the world's most diverse fauna." year="2008">Gosliner et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Here representing a first record for Thai waters
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="776BB2F3A12281959CCA342472915C83" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EE6DB6360F9A865CA2EE89EE99EEDBDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41ED029F01371AC071DD8AACA81E0F03" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
This species was mistakenly identified as 
<taxonomicName id="B43033AC92922E84323B2E31FA4E64E2" baseAuthorityName="Rudman" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Ardeadoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ardeadoris averni" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="averni">
<emphasis id="930A8C3D2B34A36FE1D989AE88A17BDC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ardeadoris averni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Rudman, 1985) by 
<bibRefCitation id="5F4E7763ACC4F40A8836E61955D31D99" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-015-0424-7" author="Mehrotra, R" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="761 - 771" refId="B161" refString="Mehrotra, R, Scott, CM, 2016. Species inventory of sea slugs (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) for Koh Tao, Thailand, with 25 first records for Thai waters. Marine Biodiversity 46: 761 - 771, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-015-0424-7" title="Species inventory of sea slugs (Gastropoda: Heterobranchia) for Koh Tao, Thailand, with 25 first records for Thai waters." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-015-0424-7" volume="46" year="2016">Mehrotra and Scott (2016)</bibRefCitation>
based on limited photographic data. Specimens found several years after initial second-hand observations have permitted reidentification, leaving 
<taxonomicName id="3F5A468E82935D924F317F8EA9AF91D2" genus="A." lsidName="A. averni" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="averni">
<emphasis id="7DF52B193AD0F55942D256AF8B081226" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">A. averni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remaining currently unrecorded in Thai waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
